WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
what is map method and how does it work

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
The map method is powerfull and wieldsy use function in javascript.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
It creates a new array based on the original one.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Let's start with an example array of numbers.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
We want to create a new array where each number is doubled.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
Using the map method, we can loop through each element.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
For each item, we return a modified value.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
Here is an example: const numbers = [1, 2, 3];

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
const doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2);

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Now, doubled will be [2, 4, 6].

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
Notice that the original array is not changed.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
The map method always returns a new array.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
This makes it very useful for functional programming.